UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1260
1 Section 2. The members of the General Assembly affirm that all political and
2 ideological disputes must be resolved through lawful, peaceful, and democratic means,
3 and commit to fostering a culture of civil discourse, tolerance, and mutual respect in the
4 Commonwealth.
